#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:5
msgid ""
"The Near Field Communication (NFC) subsystem is required to standardize the "
"NFC device drivers development and to create an unified userspace interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:8
msgid ""
"This document covers the architecture overview, the device driver interface "
"description and the userspace interface description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:12
msgid "Architecture overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:14
msgid "The NFC subsystem is responsible for:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:15
msgid "NFC adapters management;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:16
msgid "Polling for targets;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:17
msgid "Low-level data exchange;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:19
msgid ""
"The subsystem is divided in some parts. The 'core' is responsible for "
"providing the device driver interface. On the other side, it is also "
"responsible for providing an interface to control operations and low-level "
"data exchange."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:24
msgid "The control operations are available to userspace via generic netlink."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:26
msgid ""
"The low-level data exchange interface is provided by the new socket family "
"PF_NFC. The NFC_SOCKPROTO_RAW performs raw communication with NFC targets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:56
msgid "Device Driver Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:58
msgid ""
"When registering on the NFC subsystem, the device driver must inform the "
"core of the set of supported NFC protocols and the set of ops callbacks. The "
"ops callbacks that must be implemented are the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:62
msgid "start_poll - setup the device to poll for targets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:63
msgid "stop_poll - stop on progress polling operation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:64
msgid "activate_target - select and initialize one of the targets found"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:65
msgid "deactivate_target - deselect and deinitialize the selected target"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:66
msgid ""
"data_exchange - send data and receive the response (transceive operation)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:69
msgid "Userspace interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:71
msgid ""
"The userspace interface is divided in control operations and low-level data "
"exchange operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:74
msgid "CONTROL OPERATIONS:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:76
msgid ""
"Generic netlink is used to implement the interface to the control "
"operations. The operations are composed by commands and events, all listed "
"below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:79
msgid "NFC_CMD_GET_DEVICE - get specific device info or dump the device list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:80
msgid "NFC_CMD_START_POLL - setup a specific device to polling for targets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:81
msgid "NFC_CMD_STOP_POLL - stop the polling operation in a specific device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:82
msgid ""
"NFC_CMD_GET_TARGET - dump the list of targets found by a specific device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:84
msgid "NFC_EVENT_DEVICE_ADDED - reports an NFC device addition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:85
msgid "NFC_EVENT_DEVICE_REMOVED - reports an NFC device removal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:86
msgid ""
"NFC_EVENT_TARGETS_FOUND - reports START_POLL results when 1 or more targets "
"are found"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:89
msgid ""
"The user must call START_POLL to poll for NFC targets, passing the desired "
"NFC protocols through NFC_ATTR_PROTOCOLS attribute. The device remains in "
"polling state until it finds any target. However, the user can stop the "
"polling operation by calling STOP_POLL command. In this case, it will be "
"checked if the requester of STOP_POLL is the same of START_POLL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:95
msgid ""
"If the polling operation finds one or more targets, the event TARGETS_FOUND "
"is sent (including the device id). The user must call GET_TARGET to get the "
"list of all targets found by such device. Each reply message has target "
"attributes with relevant information such as the supported NFC protocols."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:100
msgid ""
"All polling operations requested through one netlink socket are stopped when "
"it's closed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:103
msgid "LOW-LEVEL DATA EXCHANGE:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:105
msgid ""
"The userspace must use PF_NFC sockets to perform any data communication with "
"targets. All NFC sockets use AF_NFC::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:115
msgid ""
"To establish a connection with one target, the user must create an "
"NFC_SOCKPROTO_RAW socket and call the 'connect' syscall with the "
"sockaddr_nfc struct correctly filled. All information comes from "
"NFC_EVENT_TARGETS_FOUND netlink event. As a target can support more than one "
"NFC protocol, the user must inform which protocol it wants to use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:121
msgid ""
"Internally, 'connect' will result in an activate_target call to the driver. "
"When the socket is closed, the target is deactivated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:124
msgid ""
"The data format exchanged through the sockets is NFC protocol dependent. For "
"instance, when communicating with MIFARE tags, the data exchanged are MIFARE "
"commands and their responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../networking/nfc.rst:128
msgid ""
"The first received package is the response to the first sent package and so "
"on. In order to allow valid \"empty\" responses, every data received has a "
"NULL header of 1 byte."
msgstr ""
